race.comment: Good little sprint. MAJOR SHARE (3) was very good in the Listed Century Stakes at Flemington last time out and is proven at 1100m, albeit his best trip is probably 1000m. He's well placed in this grade. SOUTH OF INDIA (10) is a huge weight dropper from last start, coming down 9.5kg after the claim. He's with the Dom Sutton yard now and will take plenty of catching with the featherweight. KLABEL (2) was outclassed in The Meteorite last time but his prior form was good, don't discount. WIGGUM (12) is racing well and another in light at the weights with claims.
